<TITLE> Hasina, 31 ministers take oath </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 6 (bdnews24.com)Thirty-one ministers were sworn in at a packed Bangabhaban ceremony Tuesday evening, after Sheikh Hasina took oath as the new prime minister. They include 23 cabinet members alongside Hasina, and 8 state ministers. Top cabinet posts go to the tested and more experienced hands such as Motia Chowdhury and Syed Ashraful Islam, but faces like Tanjim Ahmed alias Sohel Taj, son of the Mujibnagar government prime minister Tajuddin Ahmed, will breath fresh air into the team. Western educated and politically tested Dr Dipu Moni tops the list of women given important portfolios, alongside the likes of advocate Sahara Khatun. GM Quader represents AL's key ally Jatiya Party in the cabinet. Abul Maal Abdul Muhit, a former finance minister in the 1980s, was another notable name included in the cabinet. The full list, alongside new Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, includes: Ministers: Motia Chowdhury, Abul Maal Abdul Muhit, AK Khandaker, Syed Ashraful Islam, Abdul Latif Siddiqui, Raziuddin Razu, Advocate Sahara Khatun, Khandker Musharraf Hossain, Rezaul Karim Hira, Abul Kalam Azad, Dr AFM Ruhul Haq, Dr Afsarul Amin, Dr Abdur Razzaq, Enamul Haq Mostafa Shahid, Nurul Islam Nahid, Abdul Latif Biswash, Syed Abul Hossain, Faruq Khan, GM Quader, Ramesh Chandra Sen, Dilip Barua, Barrister Shafiq Ahmed, Dr Dipu Moni. State Ministers: Advocate Mostafizar Rahman Fizar, Captain (retd) Tazul Islam, Tanjim Ahmed Sohel, Dr Hasan Mahmud, Munnuzan Sufian, Ahad Ali Sarker, Architect Yafes Osman, Dipankar Talukdar. bdnews
